  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Write a program using a for loop to calculate the sum of the first NNN natural numbers.\n\nCheck the sample input / output below for further details.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first and only line of input contain a positive integer NNN.\n\n\nOutput Format\n\nOutput on a single line, the sum of first NNN natural numbers.",
    "constraints": [
      "1 <= T <= 100",
      "1 <= N <= 1000000",
      "All values are integers"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "First line contains an integer T, the number of test cases. Each of the next T lines contains a single integer N.",
    "outputFormat": "For each test case, output on a new line the sum of the first N natural numbers.",
    "sampleTestCases": [
      {
        "id": "sample_1",
        "input": "1\n10",
        "output": "55",
        "explanation": "For N=10, sum = 10·11/2 = 55."
